<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Speed Scrabble (Bananagrams-Style)</h2>

<p>Speed Scrabble removes the board entirely. Each player builds their own crossword grid from tiles drawn from a central pool. When someone uses all their tiles, everyone draws more. First to use all tiles when the pool empties wins.</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
    <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-400 mb-2">Pros</h3>
    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-300 list-disc pl-4 space-y-1">
      <li>No waiting for other players' turns</li>
      <li>Games last 10-15 minutes</li>
      <li>Works with 2-8 players</li>
      <li>No score tracking needed</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/10">
    <h3 class="font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-2">Cons</h3>
    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-300 list-disc pl-4 space-y-1">
      <li>No premium squares or board strategy</li>
      <li>Favours speed over vocabulary depth</li>
      <li>Harder to challenge invalid words</li>
      <li>Can feel stressful for slower thinkers</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Clabbers — Anagram Scrabble</h2>

<p>In Clabbers, words don't need to be spelled correctly — they just need to be a valid anagram of a real word. So OGDS is playable because it's an anagram of DOGS. This completely changes strategy because you never get stuck with "unplayable" letters.</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
  <p class="text-sm text-purple-300"><strong class="text-purple-400">Tournament Fact:</strong> Clabbers has its own competitive scene. Top Clabbers players can score 200+ points higher per game than standard Scrabble because any permutation of a valid word is playable.</p>
</div>

