<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Super Scrabble — The Big Board</h2>

<p>Super Scrabble uses a 21×21 board with 200 tiles, quadruple word and letter score squares, and games that can last 2+ hours. It's Scrabble on steroids.</p>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
    <h3 class="font-semibold text-amber-400 mb-2">Key Differences</h3>
    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-300 list-disc pl-4 space-y-1">
      <li>21×21 board (vs standard 15×15)</li>
      <li>200 tiles (vs 100)</li>
      <li>Quadruple word/letter squares</li>
      <li>More of every letter in the bag</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
    <h3 class="font-semibold text-purple-400 mb-2">Strategy Changes</h3>
    <ul class="text-sm text-gray-300 list-disc pl-4 space-y-1">
      <li>Bingos are easier (more tiles available)</li>
      <li>Games are longer and more strategic</li>
      <li>Board control becomes crucial</li>
      <li>More premium squares = higher scores</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Team Play Variants</h2>

<p>Team Scrabble pairs players together for collaborative decision-making. It's excellent for teaching and social play:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Consultation Teams</strong> — partners discuss plays openly during their turn. Both must agree on the final word</li>
  <li><strong>Alternating Teams</strong> — team members take turns playing, but can't discuss strategy between turns</li>
  <li><strong>Mentor-Student</strong> — experienced player coaches a beginner, explaining choices but letting them decide</li>
  <li><strong>Relay Scrabble</strong> — each team member plays one word per round, passing to the next. No one dominates</li>
</ul>

